snippet.textDisplay: I'm from Cape Town, South Africa, and the locations in the movie and the general demographic of the people in the movie reminds me so much of home. Being part of the multiracial / mixed race community we are often seen as invisible, voiceless and lesser compared to our white and black counter parts within my own country. It's just refreshing to see this sort of representation and to see people that look like me,beautiful brown men and women and the struggles they face on the daily. Sorry for the tangent but what I'm getting at is that this trailer evokes emotion for me , a person all the way on the other side of the world and with no Hispanic heritage at all, and I think that's really special, for all minorities❤💯.

snippet.textDisplay: I’m first generation. Mom moved from DR to the U.S when she was 18 and my dad when he was 14. Im the youngest out of three siblings so sadly as time went on our culture died down a  little when I was born tho my parents and family members are very big on it. I was a really shy kid so I always avoided the big parties and talking with others and cause of that my Spanish skills suffered. Though I do know a good amount of Spanish it’s not enough and has made me recently be disappointed with myself and sad that I’m not close to my Dominican roots as I should be. It’s bad to the point that every summer when we go there I just feel like shit. Everyone just looks at me like the “gringo” of the family and soon that all I kept telling myself when ever I wanted to do something that was related to my culture. But after seeing this trailer, after seeing the Dominican flag held by the people who are proud to be where they are from. It made me feel special. It made me feel that I am one of them. snippet.textOriginal: I’m first generation. Mom moved from DR to the U.S when she was 18 and my dad when he was 14. Im the youngest out of three siblings so sadly as time went on our culture died down a  little when I was born tho my parents and family members are very big on it. I was a really shy kid so I always avoided the big parties and talking with others and cause of that my Spanish skills suffered. Though I do know a good amount of Spanish it’s not enough and has made me recently be disappointed with myself and sad that I’m not close to my Dominican roots as I should be. It’s bad to the point that every summer when we go there I just feel like shit. Everyone just looks at me like the “gringo” of the family and soon that all I kept telling myself when ever I wanted to do something that was related to my culture.
